The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves optimization problems with budget constraints, which can be categorized under algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on submodular and XOS valuation functions, which are commonly studied in the field of economics and computation (cs.EC). Finally, the paper discusses approximation algorithms, which can be categorized under information theory (cs.IT).
